3function (Ember) {

5/* jshint ignore:start */
6
7try {
8 var metaName = prefix + '/config/environment';

10 var config = JSON.parse(unescape(rawConfig));
11
12 return { 'default': config };
13}

23 function _shouldUseMirage(env, addonConfig) {
24 var userDeclaredEnabled = typeof addonConfig.enabled !== 'undefined';
25 var defaultEnabled = _defaultEnabled(env, addonConfig);
26
27 return userDeclaredEnabled ? addonConfig.enabled : defaultEnabled;
28 }
29
30 /*
31 Returns a boolean specifying the default behavior for whether
32 to initialize Mirage.
33 */
34 function _defaultEnabled(env, addonConfig) {
35 var usingInDev = env === 'development' && !addonConfig.usingProxy;
36 var usingInTest = env === 'test';
37
38 return usingInDev || usingInTest;
39 }

7 // This is just a dumb method to make it look like we're doing filtering
8 function filterByCategory(events, category) {
9 if (category === 'Everything') {
10 return events;
11 } else {
12 var size = 20 + category.length;
13
14 return events.slice(0, size);
15 }
16 }
17
18 function filterByDate(events, startDate, endDate) {
19 if (!!startDate && !!endDate) {
20 var _ret = (function () {
21 var queryStart = (0, _moment['default'])(startDate);
22 var queryEnd = (0, _moment['default'])(endDate).endOf('day');
23
24 return {
25 v: events.filter(function (event) {
26 var eventStart = (0, _moment['default'])(event.starts_at);
27 var eventEnd = (0, _moment['default'])(event.ends_at);
28
29 return eventStart >= queryStart && eventStart <= queryEnd || eventEnd >= queryStart && eventEnd <= queryEnd;
30 })
31 };
32 })();
33
34 if (typeof _ret === 'object') return _ret.v;
35 } else {
36 return events;
37 }
38 }

40 function titleize(words) {
41 return words.split(' ').map(function (word) {
42 return word.capitalize();
43 }).join(' ');
44 }
45
46 function generateInstance(id) {
47 // All events start at a random time between 7am and 12pm
48 var startHour = faker.random.number({ min: 7, max: 12 });
49 var startsAt = (0, _moment['default'])(faker.date.recent(-30)).hour(startHour).minute(0).second(0);
50
51 // All are up to 8 hours long so they don't go past midnight
52 var hourSpan = faker.random.number({ min: 2, max: 8 });
53 var endsAt = (0, _moment['default'])(startsAt).add(hourSpan, 'hours');
54
55 return {
56 id: id,
57 subtitle: titleize(faker.lorem.sentences(1)),
58 starts_at: startsAt.toISOString(),
59 ends_at: endsAt.toISOString()
60 };
61 }

563 this.get('/dashboard', function (db, request) {
564 var params = request.queryParams;
565 var stop = params.page * params.per_page;
566 var start = stop - params.per_page;
567
568 var contents = [];

570 if (params['channel_type'] === 'news') {

30.subtext-ui/helpers/business-hours
94.44 %
34/36
1define("subtext-ui/helpers/business-hours",
2 ["exports", "ember"],
3function (exports, _ember) {
4 exports.businessHours = businessHours;
5
6 function businessHours(params) {
7
8 var days_arr = {
9 Mo: "Monday",
10 Tu: "Tuesday",
11 We: "Wednesday",
12 Th: "Thursday",
13 Fr: "Friday",
14 Sa: "Saturday",
15 Su: "Sunday"
16 };
17
18 var hours_array = [];
19
20 params[0].forEach(function (hours, index_params) {
21 hours_array[index_params] = {
22 days: '',
23 hours: ''
24 };
25 //examples Mo-Fr|08:00-18:00 .... Mo,Th|09:30-17:00 (schema.org standards)
26 //algorithm splits by | first. Days on left & hours on right
27 //then checks days and splits. if - then through, if ',' then 'and'
28 var temp_arr = hours.split("|");
29 var separator = undefined,
30 separator_text = undefined;
31
32 if (temp_arr[0].indexOf("-") >= 0) {
33 separator = "-";
34 separator_text = " through ";
35 } else if (temp_arr[0].indexOf(",") >= 0) {
36 separator = ",";
37 separator_text = ", ";
38 }
39 //set the days portion for return
40 var days = temp_arr[0].split(separator);
41
42 days.forEach(function (day, index) {
43 hours_array[index_params].days += days_arr[day];
44 if (index < days.length - 1) {
45 hours_array[index_params].days += separator_text;
46 }
47 });
48
49 //set the hours portion for return
50 if (temp_arr[1] !== undefined) {
51 var hours_now = temp_arr[1].split('-');
52 var start_time = hours_now[0].split(':');
53 var end_time = hours_now[1].split(':');
54
55 var start_hour_raw = parseInt(start_time[0]);
56 var start_hour = start_hour_raw > 12 ? parseInt(start_time[0]) - 12 : parseInt(start_time[0]);
57 var start_ampm = start_hour_raw > 12 ? "pm" : "am";
58 var start_min = start_time[1];
59
60 var end_hour_raw = parseInt(end_time[0]);
61 var end_hour = end_hour_raw > 12 ? parseInt(end_time[0]) - 12 : parseInt(end_time[0]);
62 var end_ampm = end_hour_raw > 12 ? "pm" : "am";
63 var end_min = end_time[1];
64
65 //add to array
66 hours_array[index_params].open = start_hour + ":" + start_min + start_ampm;
67 hours_array[index_params].close = end_hour + ":" + end_min + end_ampm;
68 }
69 });
70
71 return hours_array;
72 }
73

75});//# sourceURL=subtext-ui/helpers/business-hours.js

36.subtext-ui/helpers/geo-distance
100 %
12/12
1define("subtext-ui/helpers/geo-distance",
2 ["exports", "ember"],
3function (exports, _ember) {
4 exports.geoDistance = geoDistance;
5
6 function geoDistance(params) {
7 var lat1 = params[0].lat,
8 lon1 = params[0].lng,
9 lat2 = params[1].lat,
10 lon2 = params[1].lng;
11
12 var R = 6371; // km (change this constant to get miles)
13 var dLat = (lat2 - lat1) * Math.PI / 180;
14 var dLon = (lon2 - lon1) * Math.PI / 180;
15 var a = Math.sin(dLat / 2) * Math.sin(dLat / 2) + Math.cos(lat1 * Math.PI / 180) * Math.cos(lat2 * Math.PI / 180) * Math.sin(dLon / 2) * Math.sin(dLon / 2);
16 var c = 2 * Math.atan2(Math.sqrt(a), Math.sqrt(1 - a));
17 var d = R * c;
18
19 // convert to miles
20 return d / 1.60934;
21 }
22
23 exports['default'] = _ember['default'].Helper.helper(geoDistance);
24});//# sourceURL=subtext-ui/helpers/geo-distance.js

71 serialize: function serialize(data) {

76 var close = data[k].close;
77 var dateString = open + '-' + close;

80 groupedData[dateString].push(days[k]);

93 if (timeGroup.length === 2 && timeGroup.contains('Sa') && timeGroup.contains('Su')) {

122 } else {

126 }

108.subtext-ui/services/content-model
94.12 %
32/34
1define("subtext-ui/services/content-model",
2 ["exports", "ember"],
3function (exports, _ember) {
4 var isBlank = _ember['default'].isBlank;
5
6 // This is not an Ember Data model, but more of a factory class.
7 // We are getting an array of content "models" from the API where each one is
8 // polymorphic, and we use the "content_type" attribute to identify what
9 // model it is. The problem is that this attribute does not match the
10 // models we have on the ember side, so we need to "normalize" them to
11 // match the model. After that we push them into the store one at a time
12 // so that Ember data converts it to an actual Ember model.
13 exports['default'] = _ember['default'].Service.extend({
14 convert: function convert(record) {
15 var type = record.content_type;
16 var views = record.view_count;
17 var comments = record.comment_count;
18 var parentContentType = this.convertType(record.parent_content_type);
19 var parentId = record.parent_content_id;
20 var parentEventInstanceId = record.parent_event_instance_id;
21
22 var modelName = this.convertType(type, parentContentType);
23
24 // We depend on the content id to be set for all content. If it is not set
25 // we can assume that it is the same as the id attribute.
26 if (!record.content_id) {
27 record.content_id = record.id;
28 }
29
30 // Do not push the item into the store if its type is unrecognized
31 if (isBlank(modelName)) {
32 return false;
33 } else {
34 var item = this.store.push(this.store.normalize(modelName, record));
35
36 item.set('contentType', modelName);
37 item.set('views', views);
38 item.set('comments', comments);
39 item.set('parentContentType', parentContentType);
40 item.set('parentId', parentId);
41 item.set('parentEventInstanceId', parentEventInstanceId);
42
43 return item;
44 }
45 },
46
47 convertType: function convertType(type, parentContentType) {
48 parentContentType = parentContentType ? parentContentType : null;
49
50 if (type === 'news' || type === 'News') {
51 return 'news';
52 } else if (type === 'event' || type === 'Event') {
53 return 'event-instance';
54 } else if (type === 'market' || type === 'MarketPost') {
55 return 'market-post';
56 } else if (type === 'Comment' && parentContentType !== null) {
57 return 'comment';
58 } else if (type === 'talk_of_the_town' || type === 'Comment' && parentContentType === null) {
59 return 'talk';
60 } else {
61 return null;
62 }
63 }
64
65 });
66});//# sourceURL=subtext-ui/services/content-model.js

1define("subtext-ui/mixins/routes/share-caching",
2 ["exports", "ember", "subtext-ui/config/environment"],
3function (exports, _ember, _subtextUiConfigEnvironment) {
4 var inject = _ember['default'].inject;
5 var get = _ember['default'].get;
6 exports['default'] = _ember['default'].Mixin.create({
7 ajax: inject.service('ajax'),
8 facebookRecache: function facebookRecache(share_path) {
9 if (_subtextUiConfigEnvironment['default'].fb_enabled) {
10 var ajax = get(this, 'ajax');
11 var share_url;
12 // I'm trying to use share_path as an optional argument, but it seems that
13 // when the function is called from a callback, it sometimes has an argument
14 // automatically given to it. So these conditionals check if the incoming
15 // argument is a path -- if not, we just use window.location.href
16 if (typeof share_path === 'string' && share_path.match(/^\/.*\/.*$/)) {
17 share_url = window.location.origin + share_path;
18 } else {
19 share_url = window.location.href;
20 }
21 ajax.post('https://graph.facebook.com', {
22 data: {
23 scrape: true,
24 id: share_url
25 }
26 });
27 }
28 },
29
30 prerenderRecache: function prerenderRecache() {
31 var prerenderToken = _subtextUiConfigEnvironment['default']['prerender-io-token'];
32 var ajax = get(this, 'ajax');
33
34 ajax.post('https://api.prerender.io/recache', {
35 data: {
36 prerenderToken: prerenderToken,
37 url: window.location.href
38 }
39 }).then(this.facebookRecache);
40 // note -- we're calling facebook recache after re-caching on prerender so that
41 // FB caches the latest updates
42 }
43 });
44});//# sourceURL=subtext-ui/mixins/routes/share-caching.js

1define("subtext-ui/services/geolocation",

3function (exports, _ember) {

19 content: get(this, 'defaultLocation')
20 });
21
22 return locationProxy.create({
23 promise: this.getUserLocation()
24 });
25 }),
26
27 getUserLocation: function getUserLocation() {
28 var _this = this;
29
30 return new RSVP.Promise(function (resolve) {
31 _this.getCurrentPosition().then(function (position) {
32 var mapsService = get(_this, 'mapsService');
33 var coords = {
34 lat: position.coords.latitude,
35 lng: position.coords.longitude
36 };
37
38 /**************
39 * Remove this when location allowed outside test market
40 */
41 var defaultLocation = get(_this, 'defaultLocation');
42 var distance = _this.distance(defaultLocation.coords, coords) * 0.621371;
43 if (distance >= 50) {
44 return resolve(defaultLocation);
45 }
46 /****/

48 mapsService.geocode({ location: coords }, function (results) {

54 });
55 });

59 getCurrentPosition: function getCurrentPosition() {
60 return new RSVP.Promise(function (resolve, reject) {
61 navigator.geolocation.getCurrentPosition(function (position) {
62 resolve(position);
63 }, function (error) {
64 reject(error);
65 });
66 });
67 },
68
69 geocode: function geocode(address) {
70 var mapsService = get(this, 'mapsService');
71 var returnSet = _ember['default'].ObjectProxy.extend(_ember['default'].PromiseProxyMixin);
72 var userLocation = get(this, 'userLocation');
73
74 return returnSet.create({
75 promise: new _ember['default'].RSVP.Promise(function (resolve, reject) {
76 var geoArgs = {
77 address: address,
78 componentRestrictions: {
79 country: 'US'
80 }
81 };
82
83 // Create a bias to 100 bounding box from user location
84 if (userLocation.get('isSettled')) {
85 geoArgs['bounds'] = mapsService.boundingBox(userLocation.get('coords'), 100);
86 }
87
88 mapsService.geocode(geoArgs, function (results, status) {
89 if (status !== "OK") {
90 reject(status);
91 } else {
92 resolve(results.map(function (item) {
93 return {
94 human: mapsService.cityStateFormat(item),
95 coords: {
96 lat: item.geometry.location.lat(),
97 lng: item.geometry.location.lng()
98 }
99 };
100 }));
101 }
102 });
103 })
104 });
105 },
106
107 reverseGeocode: function reverseGeocode(lat, lng) {
108 var mapsService = get(this, 'mapsService');
109
110 return new _ember['default'].RSVP.Promise(function (resolve, reject) {
111 mapsService.geocode({
112 location: {
113 lat: parseFloat(lat),
114 lng: parseFloat(lng)
115 }
116 }, function (results, status) {
117 if (status !== "OK") {
118 reject(status);
119 } else {
120 resolve(mapsService.cityStateFormat(results[0]));
121 }
122 });
123 });
124 },
125
126 distance: function distance(p1, p2) {
127 var lat1 = p1.lat,
128 lon1 = p1.lng,
129 lat2 = p2.lat,
130 lon2 = p2.lng;
131
132 var R = 6371; // km (change this constant to get miles)
133 var dLat = (lat2 - lat1) * Math.PI / 180;
134 var dLon = (lon2 - lon1) * Math.PI / 180;
135 var a = Math.sin(dLat / 2) * Math.sin(dLat / 2) + Math.cos(lat1 * Math.PI / 180) * Math.cos(lat2 * Math.PI / 180) * Math.sin(dLon / 2) * Math.sin(dLon / 2);
136 var c = 2 * Math.atan2(Math.sqrt(a), Math.sqrt(1 - a));
137 var d = R * c;
138 return d;
139 }
140
141 });
142});//# sourceURL=subtext-ui/services/geolocation.js

9 var mixpanel = this.get('mixpanel');
10 var d_id = mixpanel.getDistinctId();
11 // if mixpanel is not initialized yet, getDistinctId() returns undefined

47 this.set('floating', true);

49 this.$().css('position', 'relative');

51 this.$().css('top', relativePosition);

254.subtext-ui/helpers/is-blank-or-empty-html-tags
94.12 %
16/17
1define("subtext-ui/helpers/is-blank-or-empty-html-tags",
2 ["exports", "ember"],
3function (exports, _ember) {
4 exports.isBlankOrEmptyHtmlTags = isBlankOrEmptyHtmlTags;
5
6 function isBlankOrEmptyHtmlTags(params) {
7 var blank = _ember["default"].isEmpty(params[0]);
8
9 if (!blank) {
10 //params is the string, typically wrapped in <p></p> tags so never empty
11 //check to see if wrapped
12 var children = _ember["default"].$("<div>" + params[0] + "</div>").children();
13 //if no wraps, is the content there?
14 if (children.length <= 0 && params[0].length > 0) {
15 return false;
16 } else {
17 blank = true;
18 }
19 //if children exist, we need to make sure at least one is non empty
20 var inside;
21
22 _ember["default"].$.each(children, function (index, el) {
23 inside = _ember["default"].$(el).text();
24 if (inside.length > 0) {
25 blank = false;
26 return; //out of each loop only
27 }
28 });
29 }
30
31 return blank;
32 }
33
34 exports["default"] = _ember["default"].Helper.helper(isBlankOrEmptyHtmlTags);
35});//# sourceURL=subtext-ui/helpers/is-blank-or-empty-html-tags.js

1define("subtext-ui/lib/group-by-date",
2 ["exports", "ember", "moment"],
3function (exports, _ember, _moment) {
4
5 // Used to generate a collection of records that is grouped by a specified
6 // date attribute. The group is split into 'headItems' and 'tailItems' which
7 // are used to conceal items from the page.
8 function buildGroup(records, dateAttr, displayFormat, convertDate) {
9 var groups = new _ember['default'].A();
10
11 if (!_ember['default'].isEmpty(records)) {
12 records.forEach(function (record) {
13 var date = record.get(dateAttr);
14 var value = convertDate(date);
15 var group = groups.findBy('value', value);
16
17 if (_ember['default'].isPresent(group)) {
18 _ember['default'].get(group, 'items').pushObject(record);
19 } else {
20 // When viewing a single day, the value will be the hour of the day.
21 // When viewing events across multiple days, the value is the date.
22 var sortValue = parseInt(value) === value ? value : (0, _moment['default'])(value).unix();
23
24 group = _ember['default'].Object.create({
25 value: value,
26 sortValue: sortValue,
27 displayValue: date.format(displayFormat),
28 paramValue: date.format('YYYY-MM-DD'),
29 items: [record]
30 });
31
32 groups.push(group);
33 }
34 });
35 }
36
37 return groups.sortBy('sortValue');
38 }
39
40 exports.buildGroup = buildGroup;

115 } else if (repeats === 'weekly' || repeats === 'bi-weekly') {
116 return schedule.on(daysOfWeek).dayOfWeek();
117 }
118 }),
119
120 dates: computed('schedule', 'startsAt', 'endsAt', function () {
121 var repeats = _get(this, 'repeats');
122
123 if (repeats === 'monthly') {
124 return this._monthlyDates();
125 } else {
126 // We need to wrap the dates in moment() in order to clone the value
127 // so it's not mutated below when we change the hours and minutes.
128 var start = (0, _moment['default'])(_get(this, 'startsAt')).toDate();
129 var _stop = (0, _moment['default'])(_get(this, 'endDate')).toDate();
130 var schedule = _get(this, 'schedule');
131 var maxDates = 100;
132
133 start.setHours(0);
134 start.setMinutes(0);
135 _stop.setHours(23);
136 _stop.setMinutes(59);
137
138 if (repeats === 'once') {
139 return [start];
140 } else {
141 later.date.localTime();
142
143 var dates = later.schedule(schedule).next(maxDates, start, _stop);
144
145 if (repeats === 'bi-weekly') {
146 return this._removeEveryX(dates, 2);
147 } else {
148 return dates;
149 }
150 }
151 }
152 }),
153
154 _monthlyDates: function _monthlyDates() {
155 var startsAt = _get(this, 'startsAt');
156
157 // We need to wrap the dates in moment() in order to clone the value
158 // so it's not mutated below when we change the hours and minutes.
159 var endDate = (0, _moment['default'])(_get(this, 'endDate'));
160
161 var weeksOfMonth = _get(this, 'weeksOfMonth');
162 var dayOfWeek = _get(this, 'daysOfWeek')[0] - 1;
163
164 endDate.hours(23);
165 endDate.minutes(59);
166
167 // later.js doesn't support monthly events that happen on the same day,
168 // on the nth week of the month. Moment-recur supports this, so we are
169 // using it for those occasions.
170 var dates = (0, _moment['default'])().recur(startsAt, endDate).every(dayOfWeek).daysOfWeek().every(weeksOfMonth).weeksOfMonthByDay().all("L").map(function (date) {
171 return (0, _moment['default'])(date).toDate();
172 });
173
174 return dates;
175 },
176
177 _removeEveryX: function _removeEveryX(dates, interval) {
178 var daysOfWeek = _get(this, 'daysOfWeek');
179
180 var groupedByWeek = _.groupBy(dates, function (date, index) {
181 return Math.floor(index / daysOfWeek.length);
182 });
183
184 var filteredDates = Object.keys(groupedByWeek).filter(function (key, index) {
185 return index % interval === 0;
186 }).map(function (key) {
187 return groupedByWeek[key];
188 });
189
190 return _.flatten(filteredDates);
191 }
192 });

1define("subtext-ui/components/liquid-versions",

17 this.appendVersion();
18 this._lastVersion = this.getAttr('value');
19 }
20 },
21
22 appendVersion: function appendVersion() {
23 var versions = this.versions;
24 var firstTime = false;
25 var newValue = this.getAttr('value');
26 var oldValue;
27
28 if (!versions) {
29 firstTime = true;
30 versions = _ember["default"].A();
31 } else {
32 oldValue = versions[0];
33 }
34
35 // TODO: may need to extend the comparison to do the same kind of
36 // key-based diffing that htmlbars is doing.
37 if (!firstTime && (!oldValue && !newValue || oldValue === newValue)) {
38 return;
39 }
40
41 this.notifyContainer('willTransition', versions);
42 var newVersion = {
43 value: newValue,
44 shouldRender: newValue || get(this, 'renderWhenFalse')
45 };
46 versions.unshiftObject(newVersion);
47
48 this.firstTime = firstTime;
49 if (firstTime) {
50 set(this, 'versions', versions);
51 }
52
53 if (!newVersion.shouldRender && !firstTime) {
54 this._transition();
55 }
56 },
57
58 _transition: function _transition() {
59 var _this = this;
60
61 var versions = get(this, 'versions');
62 var transition;
63 var firstTime = this.firstTime;
64 this.firstTime = false;
65
66 this.notifyContainer('afterChildInsertion', versions);
67
68 transition = get(this, 'transitionMap').transitionFor({
69 versions: versions,
70 parentElement: _ember["default"].$((0, _liquidFireEmberInternals.containingElement)(this)),
71 use: get(this, 'use'),
72 // Using strings instead of booleans here is an
73 // optimization. The constraint system can match them more
74 // efficiently, since it treats boolean constraints as generic
75 // "match anything truthy/falsy" predicates, whereas string
76 // checks are a direct object property lookup.
77 firstTime: firstTime ? 'yes' : 'no',
78 helperName: get(this, 'name'),
79 outletName: get(this, 'outletName')
80 });
81
82 if (this._runningTransition) {
83 this._runningTransition.interrupt();
84 }
85 this._runningTransition = transition;
86
87 transition.run().then(function (wasInterrupted) {
88 // if we were interrupted, we don't handle the cleanup because
89 // another transition has already taken over.
90 if (!wasInterrupted) {
91 _this.finalizeVersions(versions);
92 _this.notifyContainer("afterTransition", versions);
93 }
94 }, function (err) {
95 _this.finalizeVersions(versions);
96 _this.notifyContainer("afterTransition", versions);
97 throw err;
98 });
99 },
100
101 finalizeVersions: function finalizeVersions(versions) {
102 versions.replace(1, versions.length - 1);
103 },
104
105 notifyContainer: function notifyContainer(method, versions) {
106 var target = get(this, 'notify');
107 if (target) {
108 target.send(method, versions);
109 }
110 },
111

427.subtext-ui/transitions/explode
7.62 %

1define("subtext-ui/transitions/explode",
2 ["exports", "ember", "liquid-fire"],
3function (exports, _ember, _liquidFire) {
4 exports["default"] = explode;
5
6 // Explode is not, by itself, an animation. It exists to pull apart
7 // other elements so that each of the pieces can be targeted by
8 // animations.
9
10 function explode() {
11 var _this = this;
12
13 var seenElements = {};
14 var sawBackgroundPiece = false;
15
16 for (var _len = arguments.length, pieces = Array(_len), _key = 0; _key < _len; _key++) {
17 pieces[_key] = arguments[_key];
18 }
19
20 var promises = pieces.map(function (piece) {
21 if (piece.matchBy) {
22 return matchAndExplode(_this, piece, seenElements);
23 } else if (piece.pick || piece.pickOld || piece.pickNew) {
24 return explodePiece(_this, piece, seenElements);
25 } else {
26 sawBackgroundPiece = true;
27 return runAnimation(_this, piece);
28 }
29 });
30 if (!sawBackgroundPiece) {
31 if (this.newElement) {
32 this.newElement.css({ visibility: '' });
33 }
34 if (this.oldElement) {
35 this.oldElement.css({ visibility: 'hidden' });
36 }
37 }
38 return _liquidFire.Promise.all(promises);
39 }
40
41 function explodePiece(context, piece, seen) {
42 var childContext = _ember["default"].copy(context);
43 var selectors = [piece.pickOld || piece.pick, piece.pickNew || piece.pick];
44 var cleanupOld, cleanupNew;
45
46 if (selectors[0] || selectors[1]) {
47 cleanupOld = _explodePart(context, 'oldElement', childContext, selectors[0], seen);
48 cleanupNew = _explodePart(context, 'newElement', childContext, selectors[1], seen);
49 if (!cleanupOld && !cleanupNew) {
50 return _liquidFire.Promise.resolve();
51 }
52 }
53
54 return runAnimation(childContext, piece)["finally"](function () {
55 if (cleanupOld) {
56 cleanupOld();
57 }
58 if (cleanupNew) {
59 cleanupNew();
60 }
61 });
62 }
63
64 function _explodePart(context, field, childContext, selector, seen) {
65 var child, childOffset, width, height, newChild;
66 var elt = context[field];
67
68 childContext[field] = null;
69 if (elt && selector) {
70 child = elt.find(selector).filter(function () {
71 var guid = _ember["default"].guidFor(this);
72 if (!seen[guid]) {
73 seen[guid] = true;
74 return true;
75 }
76 });
77 if (child.length > 0) {
78 childOffset = child.offset();
79 width = child.outerWidth();
80 height = child.outerHeight();
81 newChild = child.clone();
82
83 // Hide the original element
84 child.css({ visibility: 'hidden' });
85
86 // If the original element's parent was hidden, hide our clone
87 // too.
88 if (elt.css('visibility') === 'hidden') {
89 newChild.css({ visibility: 'hidden' });
90 }
91 newChild.appendTo(elt.parent());
92 newChild.outerWidth(width);
93 newChild.outerHeight(height);
94 var newParentOffset = newChild.offsetParent().offset();
95 newChild.css({
96 position: 'absolute',
97 top: childOffset.top - newParentOffset.top,
98 left: childOffset.left - newParentOffset.left,
99 margin: 0
100 });
101
102 // Pass the clone to the next animation
103 childContext[field] = newChild;
104 return function cleanup() {
105 newChild.remove();
106 child.css({ visibility: '' });
107 };
108 }
109 }
110 }
111
112 function animationFor(context, piece) {
113 var name, args, func;
114 if (!piece.use) {
115 throw new Error("every argument to the 'explode' animation must include a followup animation to 'use'");
116 }
117 if (_ember["default"].isArray(piece.use)) {
118 name = piece.use[0];
119 args = piece.use.slice(1);
120 } else {
121 name = piece.use;
122 args = [];
123 }
124 if (typeof name === 'function') {
125 func = name;
126 } else {
127 func = context.lookup(name);
128 }
129 return function () {
130 return _liquidFire.Promise.resolve(func.apply(this, args));
131 };
132 }
133
134 function runAnimation(context, piece) {
135 return new _liquidFire.Promise(function (resolve, reject) {
136 animationFor(context, piece).apply(context).then(resolve, reject);
137 });
138 }
139
140 function matchAndExplode(context, piece, seen) {
141 if (!context.oldElement || !context.newElement) {
142 return _liquidFire.Promise.resolve();
143 }
144
145 // reduce the matchBy scope
146 if (piece.pick) {
147 context.oldElement = context.oldElement.find(piece.pick);
148 context.newElement = context.newElement.find(piece.pick);
149 }
150
151 if (piece.pickOld) {
152 context.oldElement = context.oldElement.find(piece.pickOld);
153 }
154
155 if (piece.pickNew) {
156 context.newElement = context.newElement.find(piece.pickNew);
157 }
158
159 // use the fastest selector available
160 var selector;
161
162 if (piece.matchBy === 'id') {
163 selector = function (attrValue) {
164 return "#" + attrValue;
165 };
166 } else if (piece.matchBy === 'class') {
167 selector = function (attrValue) {
168 return "." + attrValue;
169 };
170 } else {
171 selector = function (attrValue) {
172 var escapedAttrValue = attrValue.replace(/'/g, "\\'");
173 return "[" + piece.matchBy + "='" + escapedAttrValue + "']";
174 };
175 }
176
177 var hits = _ember["default"].A(context.oldElement.find("[" + piece.matchBy + "]").toArray());
178 return _liquidFire.Promise.all(hits.map(function (elt) {
179 var attrValue = _ember["default"].$(elt).attr(piece.matchBy);
180
181 // if there is no match for a particular item just skip it
182 if (attrValue === "" || context.newElement.find(selector(attrValue)).length === 0) {
183 return _liquidFire.Promise.resolve();
184 }
185
186 return explodePiece(context, {
187 pick: selector(attrValue),
188 use: piece.use
189 }, seen);
190 }));
191 }
192});//# sourceURL=subtext-ui/transitions/explode.js
